*Guide- Light Usage*

Please bear in mind the following are for use in Infinite Flight and are not necessarily accurate with that of real life.

NAV lights: Turned on whenever electrical power is being supplied to the aircraft. In IF’s case, whenever you turn on the “Master Switch” and should stay on throughout the duration of flight.

BEACON lights: Turned on whenever the aircraft is moving and should stay on until the aircraft comes to rest at your destination. 

LANDING lights: Turned on whenever you are cleared for takeoff and should be on at all times below 10,000ft AGL, not MSL.

STROBE lights: Turned on prior to entering an active runway and should stay on until you’re off the runway at your destination. 
